					Re: [Expansion] Reaper of Souls
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1793500">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I have the most throbbing justice boner ever right now reading that announcement. Ever since the D3 release and the epic blowback from all of the shit decisions Jay Wilson et al. made despite having a ready made formula for a great game it has been a joy watching the cognitive dissonance fade and Blizzard's PR clusterfuck lose faith in its own noise and be forced to capitulate to have any hope of saving face. Then on top of that all the Blizzard cocksuckers can't keep claiming the shit sandwich is filet minon when one has to be drugged to have any hope of enjoying the game for anywhere near the amount of time Diablo 2 was enjoyable. At least Blizzard finally admitted they were horribly wrong, and that their insistence that things were one way when they were really another was total bullshit. <br />
<br />
The worst part of it all is that the AH design was a good idea, it is just that they learned absolutely nothing from the shit design of the WoW marketplace and possessed zero economic competence throughout the AH's lifespan, which is the most embarrassing part for an allegedly AAA game company repeatedly making the same mistakes. There is actually a chance in hell I will buy the expansion now. I would have preferred that they just possess a modicum of intelligence and hire the appropriate people to unfuck the economy though. This is an acceptable half-measure though. <br />
<br />
It is another case where I hate being right though as I wanted the AH to succeed due to it reducing a swathe of issues that arise in online games like Diablo and WoW and I actually enjoy analyzing and playing the economies in games. What Blizz came up with was absurdly brain dead and devoid of any features matching with what is necessary to maintain a functioning economy in the long term.<br />
<br />
Still, I am glad to see Jay Wilson eat a mammoth, world filling amount of crow though after he was such an amazingly huge cunt to his peers and the game community. I only wish he was unemployed instead of pushing more shit ideas in video games for a premiere company.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
