		</div>
	</div>
</div>That sounds nice, however it is horribly wrong. Even just sticking to the community behavior in Diablo 2, there was a massive grey market to the point where at least one person I know was generating 20k+ USD per year addressing it, and that only captured a fraction of the overall market as he was just one person. D2JSP.org sprang up entirely because of Diablo 2's demand for goods that was not addressed by Blizzard. Pretending that demand does not exist and that the fraud/customer dissatisfaction that results from that fraud is nonexistent is immature and does a disservice to the game's community. The way Blizzard chose to address it was still fundamentally flawed though so did not remove that demand entirely and as time persisted even well. The worst part of it is that this will likely deter any future company from innovating in that space after Blizzard's incompetent efforts sabotaged themselves.
